Introduction

dearALICE is a five-member UK-based boy group under SM Entertainment and MOON&BACK MEDIA. They made their debut on February 21, 2025, with their first single "Ariana".

The members of dearALICE are James, Dexter, Olly, Reese, and Blaise.

The band's name, "dearALICE," combines the word "Dear," symbolizing a letter to their fans, with "Alice." Dexter suggested that 'ALICE' stands for 'A Love I Can't Explain." They chose the band's name after visiting a restaurant called 'Dear Alice' in Itaewon.

The band first gained attention through "Made in Korea: The K-Pop Experience," a reality show that focused on creating a British boy band using the Korean idol training system. Additionally, they made a second appearance at SMTOWN LIVE 2025 in Seoul, where they premiered their debut single, "Ariana."
